{
  "stem": "422.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The day I was deported, I was working at in the shop, as I told you about, that did the coats.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had a sleeve in the machine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Of course, whenever I could do damage, I did.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Sometimes I-- a lot of times I put in the sleeve that no soldier could put his arm in.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I sewed it down here-- he couldn't put his arm in.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Whatever I could do damage, I did.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] This was after the first uprising of the Warsaw ghetto-- in the-- in this big ghetto.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They ordered everybody down.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Everybody.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was on this street, a couple shops-- [INAUDIBLE] inside the shop, [INAUDIBLE] at this shop.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Every shop, they were working for the Germans, the-- the things that they need for the war.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We were ordered to street.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When everybody was assembled, they took up to the umschlagplatz.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "On the way to that umschlagplatz, from where the trains went away, we-- we past the big ghetto.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We-- we passed the big ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we had to-- we stepped on boiling pieces of wood, boiling bricks that fell from the-- from the uprising.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Still was burning in our feet.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "That's how we came to the umschlagplatz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I tell you, over there it was a terrible thing to be.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "That umschlagplatz, I never forget.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Never forget.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We were treated like-- not even like animals.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Hit and sick-- sick people were laying, people with children, people were vomiting, people were-- it's horrible to even talk about it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "That took us like a day and a night, till they-- because the trains left and when they were filled up already, we have to wait until we were going to unload in Treblinka or in other places, the people.",
      "word_count": 40
    }
  ],
